Show Description

From the Infowars web site :: On the Tuesday, November 26 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Infowars Nightly News anchor David Knight fills in, breaking down the gradual implementation of a biometric police state where law enforcement keeps tabs on citizens through traffic cameras, thumbprint scans and facial identification, enabling more sadistic police, but with less accountability for corrupt behavior. 

On today's show, David speaks with reporter Jakari Jackson about the implications of the most obvious human inventory database, Facebook. We'll also hear from Storyleak editor Anthony Gucciardi about how the psychological societal controls of the elite and how political correctness is enforced to keep the public in check. 

Alex Jones kicks off today's broadcast analyzing the Iranian nuclear situation and the "coincidental" timing of an Israeli air force drill.
